  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Solar-Powered Water Distribution Systems</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Solar-powered piped water supplies: In partnership with the John Snow Institute (JSI), WHI has constructed solar-powered water supply systems for 12 Health Posts in Sierra Leone, providing access to the water needed to properly clean and disinfect facilities. They also provide clean, safe drinking water to staff and patients. Our solar-powered water supplies consist of a well, a water tower and solar panels that generate power for an electric pump. Water towers create the possibility of running water piped into a building, something that is a rarity in Sierra Leone. A hand pump is also installed in the same well as a backup pump in case any issues arise with the solar power generation &#x2014; a feature unique to WHI&#x2019;s model.

In 2017, WHI will be constructing 49 more of these solar powered water systems at health posts for DFID/UKAID and JSI.</narrative>
  </description>
